<p><b>Suzanna Arundhati Roy</b> (born 24 November, 1961) is an Indian <a href="/wiki/Writer" title="Writer">writer</a> and <a href="/wiki/Activist" title="Activist" class="mw-redirect">activist</a> who won the <a href="/wiki/Booker_Prize" title="Booker Prize" class="mw-redirect">Booker Prize</a> in 1997 for her novel, <i><a href="/wiki/The_God_of_Small_Things" title="The God of Small Things">The God of Small Things</a></i>, and in 2002, the <a href="/wiki/Lannan_Foundation" title="Lannan Foundation" class="mw-redirect">Lannan</a> Cultural Freedom Prize.</p>
